block.documentation:
The Communications Subsystem enables two-way data transfer between the AOMS and ground control. It features both Low Rate and High Rate Antennas for transmitting telemetry data, system logs, and manufacturing reports. RF Transmitters and Receivers are used to handle data communication over radio frequencies, while the Duplexer and High Rate Transmitter Amplifier ensure that large amounts of data, such as production logs or system health telemetry, are sent to Earth with minimal loss.
Managed by the Communication CSC, this subsystem continuously monitors and maintains a stable link with ground stations, ensuring that the AOMS can receive commands and transmit performance data in real-time. The combination of high and low-rate communication channels allows the spacecraft to prioritize critical telemetry while offloading less time-sensitive data when bandwidth permits.
